President Trump visited the Yuma Border Patrol Station in Arizona to commemorate the completion of over 200 miles of the border wall. He praised the wall as a powerful and comprehensive structure with advanced technology. Acting Secretary of Homeland Security Chad Wolf and other officials also spoke about the progress made in securing the border and reducing illegal immigration. They highlighted the decrease in illegal border crossings and the seizure of drugs and apprehension of criminal aliens. The President and other officials expressed gratitude for the support of law enforcement and emphasized the importance of border security for national security. They also mentioned the success of the wall in preventing the spread of COVID-19 and the need to protect statues and monuments from vandalism. The President thanked the officials and expressed his commitment to completing the border wall by the end of the year.